(Preliminary) README for asciibrot
==================================

asciibrot can render images of the Mandelbrot set and Julia sets. It has
three modes:

	- Mandelbrot (default)
	- Julia
	- Animated Julia

asciibrot has only been tested in an XTerm and a Linux VT.


Options
-------

  -c CHARSET, --charset=CHARSET
                        Charset. Defaults to " .:-+=oO0#".
  -C INCHAR, --inchar=INCHAR
                        Character *inside* the set. Defaults to "@".
  -i ITERATIONS, --iterations=ITERATIONS
                        Number of iterations. Defaults to 30.
  -z ZOOM, --zoom=ZOOM  Smaller means more zooming in. Defaults to 1.
  -p POSITION, --position=POSITION
                        Coordinate, like "1.08:0.42". Defaults to 0:0.
  -J JULIAPARAM, --juliaparam=JULIAPARAM
                        Julia parameter, like "-0.46:0.58". Defaults to
                        -0.46:0.58.
  -j, --julia           Draw a Julia set. Defaults to False.
  -f FONTASPECT, --fontaspect=FONTASPECT
                        Font aspect ratio. If your font is 8x16, you need to
                        set this to "0.5". Defaults to 0.5.
  -a, --animate         Animate a Julia set. Defaults to False.
  -b, --no-bounce       Zoom in and out when animating. Defaults to True.
  -d DELAY, --delay=DELAY
                        Delay for animation mode. Defaults to 0.1.
  -s SIZE, --size=SIZE  Size of the image. Defaults to current terminal size
                        (101x79).


Examples
--------

Of course, the larger your terminal, the better the results. I suggest
to use a program like xaos[1] or my own multifrac[2] to actually explore
the sets. You'll also have to learn how to "read" the ASCII images. :-)

[1] http://sourceforge.net/projects/xaos/
[2] https://github.com/vain/Multifrac


$ asciibrot -p '-0.5:0' -s '80x24'

                                    ...........::+:-@......
                                 .............::-=+::........
                               .............:-=@@@@=@:.........
